{"parse":{"title":"Lambert summation","pageid":19080350,"revid":790712517,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>In <a href=\"/wiki/Mathematical_analysis\" title=\"Mathematical analysis\">mathematical analysis</a>, <b>Lambert summation</b> is a summability method for a class of <a href=\"/wiki/Divergent_series\" title=\"Divergent series\">divergent series</a>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Definition\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Definition</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Examples\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Examples</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Definition\">Definition</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Lambert_summation&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Definition\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>A series <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle \\sum a_{n}}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mo>&#x2211;<!-- \u2211 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle \\sum a_{n}}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/2993f473f311220169d2c33a446013bc8d6ca2d7\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -1.338ex; width:6.19ex; height:3.843ex;\" alt=\"\\sum a_{n}\"/></span> is <i>Lambert summable</i> to <i>A</i>, written <span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle \\sum a_{n}=A\\,(\\mathrm {L} )}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mo>&#x2211;<!-- \u2211 --></mo>\n        <msub>\n          <mi>a</mi>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </msub>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\" />\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle \\sum a_{n}=A\\,(\\mathrm {L} )}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/d4e92a6a9024cd8ba81fa0f0139e06479c3bee3f\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -1.338ex; width:14.681ex; height:3.843ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle \\sum a_{n}=A\\,(\\mathrm {L} )}\"/></span>, if\n</p>\n<dl><dd><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle \\lim _{r\\rightarrow 1-}(1-r)\\sum _{n=1}^{\\infty }{\\frac {na_{n}r^{n}}{1-r^{n}}}=A.}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <munder>\n          <mo movablelimits=\"true\" form=\"prefix\">lim</mo>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>r</mi>\n            <mo stretchy=\"false\">&#x2192;<!-- \u2192 --></mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n            <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n          </mrow>\n        </munder>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n        <mi>r</mi>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n        <munderover>\n          <mo>&#x2211;<!-- \u2211 --></mo>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n            <mo>=</mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#x221E;<!-- \u221e --></mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </munderover>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>n</mi>\n              <msub>\n                <mi>a</mi>\n                <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msub>\n              <msup>\n                <mi>r</mi>\n                <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n            </mrow>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>1</mn>\n              <mo>&#x2212;<!-- \u2212 --></mo>\n              <msup>\n                <mi>r</mi>\n                <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                  <mi>n</mi>\n                </mrow>\n              </msup>\n            </mrow>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mi>A</mi>\n        <mo>.</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle \\lim _{r\\rightarrow 1-}(1-r)\\sum _{n=1}^{\\infty }{\\frac {na_{n}r^{n}}{1-r^{n}}}=A.}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/9a8e457e3a2b243dd138866ab2237963b3b11804\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -3.005ex; width:28.07ex; height:6.843ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle \\lim _{r\\rightarrow 1-}(1-r)\\sum _{n=1}^{\\infty }{\\frac {na_{n}r^{n}}{1-r^{n}}}=A.}\"/></span></dd></dl>\n<p>If a series is convergent to <i>A</i> then it is Lambert summable to <i>A</i> (an <a href=\"/wiki/Abelian_theorem\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Abelian theorem\">Abelian theorem</a>).\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Examples\">Examples</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Lambert_summation&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Examples\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle \\sum _{n=1}^{\\infty }{\\frac {\\mu (n)}{n}}=0(\\mathrm {L} )}\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <munderover>\n          <mo>&#x2211;<!-- \u2211 --></mo>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi>n</mi>\n            <mo>=</mo>\n            <mn>1</mn>\n          </mrow>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">&#x221E;<!-- \u221e --></mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </munderover>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mfrac>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>&#x03BC;<!-- \u03bc --></mi>\n              <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n              <mi>n</mi>\n              <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n            </mrow>\n            <mi>n</mi>\n          </mfrac>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mn>0</mn>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo>\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle \\sum _{n=1}^{\\infty }{\\frac {\\mu (n)}{n}}=0(\\mathrm {L} )}</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/f17a4a8b1ebdd6ccc0014742e32a5a3ba37ee4f8\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -3.005ex; width:16.707ex; height:6.843ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle \\sum _{n=1}^{\\infty }{\\frac {\\mu (n)}{n}}=0(\\mathrm {L} )}\"/></span>, where &#956; is the <a href=\"/wiki/M%C3%B6bius_function\" title=\"M\u00f6bius function\">M\u00f6bius function</a>.  Hence if this series converges at all, it converges to zero.</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Lambert_summation&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Lambert_series\" title=\"Lambert series\">Lambert series</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Abel%E2%80%93Plana_formula\" title=\"Abel\u2013Plana formula\">Abel\u2013Plana formula</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Abelian_and_tauberian_theorems\" title=\"Abelian and tauberian theorems\">Abelian and tauberian theorems</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Lambert_summation&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><cite class=\"citation book\">Jacob Korevaar (2004). <i>Tauberian theory. A century of developments</i>. Grundlehren der Mathematischen Wissenschaften. <b>329</b>. <a href=\"/wiki/Springer-Verlag\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Springer-Verlag\">Springer-Verlag</a>. p.&#160;18. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/3-540-21058-X\" title=\"Special:BookSources/3-540-21058-X\">3-540-21058-X</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Tauberian+theory.+A+century+of+developments&amp;rft.series=Grundlehren+der+Mathematischen+Wissenschaften&amp;rft.pages=18&amp;rft.pub=Springer-Verlag&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.isbn=3-540-21058-X&amp;rft.au=Jacob+Korevaar&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ALambert+summation\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></li>\n<li><cite class=\"citation book\"><a href=\"/wiki/Hugh_Montgomery_(mathematician)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Hugh Montgomery (mathematician)\">Hugh L. Montgomery</a>; <a href=\"/wiki/Robert_Charles_Vaughan_(mathematician)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Robert Charles Vaughan (mathematician)\">Robert C. Vaughan</a> (2007). <i>Multiplicative number theory I. Classical theory</i>. Cambridge tracts in advanced mathematics. <b>97</b>. Cambridge: Cambridge Univ. Press. pp.&#160;159\u2013160. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-521-84903-9\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-521-84903-9\">0-521-84903-9</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Mu